The paper deals with the task of robust nonlinear regression, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The use of kernels and reproducing kernel Hilbert spaces suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The application of the proposed method to image denoising suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The use of sparse modeling and greedy algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. Finally, the theoretical analysis of the proposed method suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
